agriculture</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../789/29789.xml">
tourism</link>. Nyons is the center of the local <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../479/22479.xml">
olive tree</link> cultivation with numerous oil mills, an <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link> cooperative and an olive tree/olive oil museum. The olives grown in Nyons and les Baronnies have an AOC (<link>
Appellation d'Origine Contrôlée</link>) quality label.</p>
<p>

